Loyal Member of Giliath Lang</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usollaiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sollaiel</A> at: 7/29/02 7:58:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/29/02 11:39:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Why does it follow that resists should be lowered to compensate for the fact that spell dmg is reduced?<br>
<br>
Spell dmg is nerfed in pvp for a very simple reason.  The game as a whole was designed with pve in mind and balanced with pve in mind.  Consequently spell dmg is too great for pvp. Thus its nerfed.<br>
<br>
I don't see how it follows from the above that resists also need to be nerfed by the same degree. <br>
<br>
&quot;Plus.. I don't feel sorry for any of the classes that eat a good manaburn  Afterall, the Melee has the upper hand by far already.&quot;<br>
<br>
What melees? All of them? I don't think so.  Maybe 60 pally/sk are overpowered.  NTOV equiped melee probably are.  What about the rest of us?  What about the fact that its unbalanced vs all classes not just melees?  What about the fact that the whole above statement is utterly flawed? <br>
<br>
Your saying melees are overpowered vs casters its fair to make one caster class grossly overpowered vs all melee, all casters, and all priests. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/29/02 12:20:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Ok, so spell damaged was designed for pve in mind. Exactly what was melee damage designed for?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usollaiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sollaiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/30/02 4:31:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> No, and the change I proposed has nothing to do with PvE. <br>
