<BR>
44th Season, Paladin of Life
<BR>
Loyal Member of Giliath Lang</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukainite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kainite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/30/02 8:20:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I think we all agree...</span><hr size=1> I think we all agree that at least the resists are out of whack for the most part, due to twinkage. This makes it immposible for the casters to get effective spells off without being resisted (their are some notable exceptions, but mostly HIGH level, such as some magic based DoTs like splurt, Winged Death, and Lures and such). The problem is that Verant's solution, while a good idea in theory to me, of suggested levels (making them not work well below them also) is so out of whack, it's retarded. They have the level restrictions on some things so high they will never get used, cause you can get something equal or better from an easier and lower level mob to fight somewhere else. <br>
<br>
Another idea is to cap resistances on a per level basis for PvP. But again that has inherent flaws (what is an acceptable level, and to whom is it acceptable). Suffice it to say, at level 15 vs level 15, root should not be resisted on average of 14 out of 15 times. If done properly it may alleviate some of the caster griefs with twinkage at lower levels in PvP (the damage cap helps balance the weapons a bit, in my opinion). The biggest complaint is as always, twinkage of melee far outweighs twinkage of casters (great I have 220 Int or Wis, does not help save me from getting spanked by similiarly twinked warrior).<br>
<br>
As it stands, PvP is about 60-70 (at least) percent gear based. Skill can only take you so far if you can't land nukes, or in melee you hit for 80's max and get hit for 150+ each pass (even out jousting 3 hits to 1, you will most likely lose with the lesser damage output). At higher levels some of this starts to change, but I think it only changes at the extreme high end (say 55+). And that is due to your level catching up to the gear (or ability to get some of the twinkage gear). Some classes are inherently flawed too (enchanter cannot lower MR more than a Shaman can..???) but that is another topic as always. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usollaiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sollaiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/30/02 10:20:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think we all agree...</span><hr size=1> I have to agree there.. <br>
