Loyal Member of Giliath Lang</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usollaiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sollaiel</A> at: 7/30/02 10:22:29 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/30/02 5:11:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think we all agree...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Ok, so spell damaged was designed for pve in mind. Exactly what was melee damage designed for? &quot;<br>
<br>
Melee dmg was indeed designed for pve as well but it allready carries its own inherent nerf for pvp. Specificly in pve the melee range bug isn't an issue.  This weakens melees enough as it is.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cleric can't get a nuke through 98% of the time in PvP.. That's fair?&quot;<br>
<br>
Clerics are enourmously strong defensively.  They can outheal any manna based dmg dealer and outlast any duel wielder with ds (coldain ring or shaman potion) + heals.  Short of MB a high lvl cleric should be unkillable 1 vs 1.  Just their presence swings a group fight enourmously towards whichever side they support.  They shouldn't be very strong offensively.  That being so Judgement was still hitting me for 2-450 dmg through 190 mr the other day.<br>
<br>
&quot;Last night, my humble 10 Wizard couldn't get a nuke off on a Level 10 SK!&quot;<br>
<br>
My resist cap suggestion would fix that...<br>
<br>
&quot;Twinkage or no.. The resist system is fried..&quot;<br>
<br>
At low levels its friend purely because of twinkage.  Fix the twinkage aleviate the problem entirely for those levels. <br>
<br>
&quot;Even at 46, my paladin can't get root to stick on anyone his level.. How is that balanced?&quot;<br>
<br>
Roots/snares/blinds should be 100% resistable at high lvls with the apropriate resist gear.  Know why? Because roots/blinds/snares that weren't would be enourmoustly overpowered.  If your roots did indeed stick reliably at that point would any caster even stand a chance?<br>
